given an int return the value of all individual digits added together.

will there be any negative numbers. there could be.
all returns will be positive.
will be a valid int returned.

input = 125
output = 8

*/
seperate each number of the int and add them together
while loop
% each number then divide the input by \10 to remove the number and continue in the cycle
return the added int value 
\*

public static int AddingDigits(int input)
{
	int output = 0;
	while(input != 0)
	{
		output += input % 10;
		input /= 10;
	}
	if(output < 0)
	{
		output *= -1;
	}
	return output;
}
